<p color="yellow">Breeze::OS Installer Setup -- Boot Loader Settings</p>
<p>
You <b>must</b> enable <font color="#33FB01"><b>boot configuration</b></font> by selecting a <b>boot loader</b>.<br>The <b>boot configuration</b> will allow you to <b>boot</b> your new installation.<br>It also allows <b>booting</b> a <font color="#33FB01"><b>Windows</b></font> installation, if any present.<br>
The following boot loaders are available:
<ul>
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>Syslinux</b></font> the recommended boot loader.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>Grub</b></font> GRand Unified Boot loader.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>Gummiboot</b></font> Gummiboot, a UEFI Boot loader.
<li><font color="#33FB01"><b>Lilo</b></font> LInux LOader, the classic OS boot loader.
</ul>
The set of offered <b>boot loaders</b> is based on your <b>partitioning</b> mode,<br>your <b>root</b> partition filesystem, and your <b>kernel</b> selection.<br>
The <font color="#33FB01"><b>Syslinux</b></font> boot loader only handles<br>the <b>VFAT</b>, <b>Ext3</b>, <b>Ext4</b>, or <b>Btrfs</b> filesystem, as the <b>boot</b> filesystem.<br>
The <b>Btrfs</b> filesystem is not available in this release.
</p>
<p>
Select a <b>boot loader</b>, or click on <a href="action=continue"><img width="16" height="16" src="install/images/next.png"></a> to <b>Continue</b>.
</p>
